This is my favorite go-to for an Asian restaurant. The owner and her husband are always super sweet to my mother and me. I don’t eat shrimp or pork, but my mother does. However, they are well aware of my dietary needs and will label everything properly.  Quick story: My office is down the street and I ordered lunch for my coworkers (which included shrimp and pork). When I picked up my order the owner asked if I was feeling okay. That’s how concerned she is about her customers.  Also, this restaurant does not use MSG. And have some great vegetarian options.  The only drawback is I had to give one, is that they are not open on Sundays. But, this is understandable because of the large amount of prep work that I would assume any restaurant has to do.  If you prefer to order via an app, I recommend ordering via DoorDash.

Called this place for the first time tonight and the lady who picked up the phone accused me of placing an order and never coming to pick it up. I said Ma’am this my first time calling. She then gets loud and say you did but if you hurry I can make it for you now. Uuummm no Ma’am! You will not accused me of something I didn’t do and then think I’m going to let you fix my food. I don’t even play like that. Again this was my first time calling this Place and it will be my last. Never have I ever placed an order anywhere and didn’t pick it up. I don’t play about my food and to be accused like that I’m so upset. I’m over blew because I really wanted Chinese but they will never get my money, not after the way I was treated.

This is my first time ordering from this restaurant. I was hesitant having never ordered from here before. But we live less than a mile from here and we wanted something quick. I got the beef chow mein and chicken with peapods. They said 20 minutes and the order was ready when I arrived at under 20 minutes. I was pleasantly surprised. The beef and the chicken were both very very tender and hot. Both had a good flavor. It's a take out place that's sit down restaurant quality. That's all that needs to be said. I will happily order from here from now on.

This Kenwood restaurant may be short on looks, but it is big on consistently delicious meals and great customer service.  As a vegetarian, I really like the fact that they offer meals where the customer gets to choose the protein of their choice, mine is often tofu.  My favorites are veggie fried rice, veggie egg rolls, ma po tofu, and the fresh fruit smoothies.  Being in walking distance, having late hours and delivery make a mainstay for me and my friends.  My only wish would be for the dining room to be more appealing.  Alas, because I live so close, I simply do takeout.
